cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.SD

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the purview of cs.CL.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed Select-Additive Learning (SAL) procedure is a machine learning method that improves the generalizability of trained discriminative neural networks. Hence, this paper could also be categorized under cs.LG.
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper deals with multimodal sentiment analysis, which involves analyzing sentiment from multiple modalities such as text, audio, and video. This falls under the purview of cs.CV, which deals with computer vision and pattern recognition.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with multimodal sentiment analysis, which involves analyzing sentiment from multiple modalities such as text, audio, and video. This falls under the purview of cs.MM, which deals with multimedia.
5. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper deals with sentiment analysis from audio, which falls under the purview of cs.SD, which deals with sound.
